title: Where is the pywrap_tensorflow_internal.lib after building TensorFlow1.11 On Win10?
body_html: I have build TensorFlow1.11GPU version successfully in Win10 with using bazel, and generate tensorflow-1.11.0rc1-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl file seccessfully. But I can not find the C++ lib(pywrap_tensorflow_internal.lib), where is the lib? I want to use C++ not Python.

body:
I have build TensorFlow1.11GPU version successfully in Win10 with using bazel, and generate tensorflow-1.11.0rc1-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl file seccessfully. But I can not find the C++ lib(pywrap_tensorflow_internal.lib), where is the lib?  I want to use C++ not  Python.
